00:13:45.940 --> 00:13:48.356
chairperson, PricewaterhouseCoopers,

00:13:48.380 --> 00:13:50.420
he asked me to include it in my talk.

00:13:52.780 --> 00:13:55.660
We need to grow support lines
and help groups,

00:13:56.300 --> 00:13:58.260
so victims can help each other

00:13:59.060 --> 00:14:01.876
when their lives and finances
have been derailed.

00:14:01.900 --> 00:14:06.276
We must as individuals disrupt
gender violence as it is happening.

00:14:06.300 --> 00:14:08.076
92 percent of young people

00:14:08.100 --> 00:14:09.900
29 and under witness it.

00:14:10.540 --> 00:14:13.020
72 percent of us have witnessed it.

00:14:13.900 --> 00:14:15.636
We must have the courage and urgency

00:14:15.660 --> 00:14:18.340
to practice stopping it
as it is unfolding.

00:14:20.060 --> 00:14:21.260
And lastly,

00:14:22.540 --> 00:14:23.740
believe her.

00:14:25.420 --> 00:14:26.636
Believe her.

00:14:26.660 --> 00:14:29.140
(Applause)

00:14:33.540 --> 00:14:37.380
This is fundamentally
a problem of human interaction.

00:14:38.380 --> 00:14:42.516
And as I believe that human interaction
is at the core of our healing,

00:14:42.540 --> 00:14:46.540
trauma not transformed
will be trauma transferred.

00:14:47.420 --> 00:14:50.516
Edith Wharton said,
"The end is latent in the beginning,"

00:14:50.540 --> 00:14:55.516
so we are going to end this talk
replacing hate speech with love speech.

00:14:55.540 --> 00:14:57.476
Because I get lonely in this,

00:14:57.500 --> 00:14:59.340
but I know that we are allies.

00:15:00.460 --> 00:15:02.116
I recently learned

00:15:02.140 --> 00:15:06.756
about how gratitude and affirmations
offset negative interactions.

00:15:06.780 --> 00:15:10.236
It takes five of those
to offset one negative interaction,

00:15:10.260 --> 00:15:11.716
and gratitude in particular --

00:15:11.740 --> 00:15:14.436
free, available globally
any time, anywhere,

00:15:14.460 --> 00:15:16.556
to anyone in any dialect --

00:15:16.580 --> 00:15:19.796
it fires the pregenual anterior cingulate,

00:15:19.820 --> 00:15:21.636
a watershed part of the brain

00:15:21.660 --> 00:15:24.276
that floods it with great, good stuff.

00:15:24.300 --> 00:15:26.916
So I'm going to say
awesome stuff about myself.

00:15:26.940 --> 00:15:29.276
I would like for you
to reflect it back to me.

00:15:29.300 --> 00:15:31.436
It might sound something like this --

00:15:31.460 --> 00:15:32.916
(Laughter)

00:15:32.940 --> 00:15:36.956
I am a powerful and strong woman,
and you would say, "Yes, you are."

00:15:36.980 --> 00:15:38.636
Audience: Yes, you are.

00:15:38.660 --> 00:15:40.396
Ashley Judd: My mama loves me.

00:15:40.420 --> 00:15:41.836
A: Yes, she does.

00:15:41.860 --> 00:15:43.916
AJ: I did a great job with my talk.

00:15:43.940 --> 00:15:45.556
A: Yes, you did.

00:15:45.580 --> 00:15:48.716
AJ: I have a right to be here.

00:15:48.740 --> 00:15:50.516
A: Yes, you do.

00:15:50.540 --> 00:15:51.756
AJ: I'm really cute.

00:15:51.780 --> 00:15:53.036
(Laughter)

00:15:53.060 --> 00:15:54.516
A: Yes, you are.

00:15:54.540 --> 00:15:56.276
AJ: God does good work.

00:15:56.300 --> 00:15:58.076
A: Yes, He does.

00:15:58.100 --> 00:15:59.836
AJ: And I love you.

00:15:59.860 --> 00:16:02.180
Thank you so much
for letting me be of service.

00:16:03.140 --> 00:16:04.356
Bless you.

00:16:04.380 --> 00:16:09.550
(Applause)

